<DocLayout title="Press" description="AEGIS Initiative press releases, published articles, and media resources.">
  <h1>Press</h1>

  <p>
    Press releases, published articles, and media resources from the AEGIS Initiative.
  </p>

  <hr />

  <section>
    <h2>Publications</h2>
    <p>
      Preprints and formal submissions from the AEGIS Initiative. Peer-reviewed
      versions will be linked when published.
    </p>

    <h3>IEEE Computer — Special Issue on AI Governance and Compliance</h3>
    <p>
      <strong>"AEGIS: A Constitutional Governance Architecture for Autonomous AI Agents"</strong><br />
      Kenneth Tannenbaum, AEGIS Initiative. Submitted March 2026.<br />
      DOI: <a href="https://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.19223924">10.5281/zenodo.19223924</a>
    </p>
    <p>
      Presents AEGIS as a constitutional governance architecture that enforces
      deterministic policy at the agent action boundary — post-reasoning,
      pre-execution. Satisfies Anderson's reference monitor properties, aligns
      with all four functions of the NIST AI Risk Management Framework, and
      introduces a decentralized federation model for cross-organizational
      governance intelligence sharing.
    </p>

    <h3>IEEE Data Descriptions</h3>
    <p>
      <strong>"ATX-1: AEGIS Threat Matrix for AI Governance Systems"</strong><br />
      Kenneth Tannenbaum, AEGIS Initiative. Submitted March 2026.<br />
      DOI: <a href="https://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.19251098">10.5281/zenodo.19251098</a>
    </p>
    <p>
      Machine-readable threat intelligence dataset in STIX 2.1 format. 10 tactics,
      29 techniques cataloging failure modes specific to autonomous AI agents
      interacting with operational infrastructure. Grounded in the Agents of Chaos
      study (Shapira et al. 2026) and validated through adversarial testing of
      the AEGIS reference implementation.
    </p>

    <h3>NIST AI Risk Management Framework</h3>
    <p>
      <strong>"AEGIS: A Constitutional Governance Architecture — NIST AI RMF Position Statement"</strong><br />
      Finnoybu IP LLC. Submitted March 7, 2026.
    </p>
    <p>
      Unsolicited position statement proposing architectural governance as a
      complementary layer to existing AI risk management approaches. References
      the AEGIS Constitution v0.1.1.
    </p>

    <h3>NCCoE — AI Agent Identity &amp; Access Management</h3>
    <p>
      <strong>"AEGIS: AI Agent Identity, Authorization, and Governance"</strong><br />
      Finnoybu IP LLC. Submitted March 2026.
    </p>
    <p>
      Response to the National Cybersecurity Center of Excellence (NCCoE) project
      on AI Agent Identity and Access Management. Proposes constitutional
      governance as a framework for agent identity binding, capability-based
      authorization, and deterministic enforcement.
    </p>
  </section>

  <hr />

  <section>
    <h2>Software Releases</h2>

    <h3>aegis-core v0.1.2 — Stable Reference Implementation</h3>
    <p>
      Released March 31, 2026.<br />
      DOI: <a href="https://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.19355478">10.5281/zenodo.19355478</a> |
      <a href="https://github.com/aegis-initiative/aegis-core/releases/tag/v0.1.2">GitHub Release</a>
    </p>
    <p>
      Python reference implementation of the AEGIS governance enforcement engine.
      403 tests, 100% ATX-1 technique coverage, 9 rounds of adversarial red/blue
      team testing. Implements the AEGIS Governance Protocol (AGP-1) with
      five-dimension risk scoring, capability-based access control, and immutable
      audit trail.
    </p>

    <h3>ATX-1 v2.1 — AEGIS Threat Matrix</h3>
    <p>
      Released March 27, 2026.<br />
      DOI: <a href="https://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.19251098">10.5281/zenodo.19251098</a> |
      <a href="https://aegis-governance.com">aegis-governance.com</a>
    </p>
    <p>
      10 tactics, 29 techniques cataloging agentic AI failure modes.
      Machine-readable STIX 2.1 threat intelligence. Includes TA010
      (Act Beyond Governance Interpretation) — a novel tactic discovered
      during adversarial testing.
    </p>
  </section>

